 time, time gone astray, asprawl....

War in the Far East allowed my father that happy activity which helped him — if not to forget Virginia — at least to make life worth living again. His vigorous egotism was but a form of manly vitality and as such wholly consistent with an essentially generous nature. Permanent misery, let alone self-destruction, must have seemed to him a mean business, a shameful surrender. When in 1905 he married again, he surely felt satisfaction at having got the uppe